{"lemma":"بابٌ","slug":"بابٌ","root":"ب.#.ب","root_slug":"ب-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"باب","root":"بوب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":27},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3500"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"door, gate","examples":[{"text":"وَادْخُلُوا الْبَابَ سُجَّدًا وَقُولُوا حِطَّةٌ","english":"[And] enter the gate with humility …"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"opening, gateway"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"entrance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gullet, weasand","examples":[{"text":"وقد تخرج للدابة من حنكها ويسمي التحنيك وصفة العمل في ذلك إذا أحنكت الدابة فأفتح لها من الدرجة الثالثة والرابعة ولا تفتح لها قرب الباب لأن الدم ربما عسر إمساكه فتلف الدابة.","english":"One may extract the blood from the jaw of a beast and it is called taḥnīk and the operation consists in that you have bound the beast with a chinstrap and now cut it open to the third or fourth degree but don’t open it close the throat as it may be difficult to contain the blood and the beast will succumb."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"opportunity, a chance, opening"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"military tactic, maneuver, an opening to use a strategy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chapter, section, column"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"group, class, category"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"appearance of an astronomical body, a juncture, an opening to observe"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"domain, field","tags":["figuratively"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Usually considered a borrowing from Aramaic בָּבָא (bāḇā, “gate”), from Akkadian 𒆍 (bābum, “gate”), particularly since the Arabs, living in tents, did not need doors. However, Hans Bauer considers all of these words native, explaining the formation as an ancient univerbation of etyma equivalent to Arabic بَاءَ (bāʔa) بِ (bi) “he has entered into (the house)”."},"ipa":["/baːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3500","headword_ar":"بَابٌ","root":"bwb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawabN","text_ar":"بَوَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A door; a gate; a place of entrance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing with which a place of entrance, such as a door"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gate, is closed; of wood &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abowaAbN","text_ar":"اَبْوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biybaAnN","text_ar":"بِيبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abowibapN","text_ar":"اَبْوِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) [a pl. of pauc., said to be] only used for conformity with another word mentioned therewith, as in the saying (of Ibn-Mukbil, so in a copy of the S),"},{"kind":"quote","text":"hat~aAku A^axobiyapK wa l~aAju A^abowibapK"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A frequent render of tents, a frequent enterer of doors"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, M,) not being allowable when occurring alone; (S;) but IAar and Lh assert that it is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAb","text_ar":"باب"},{"kind":"text","text":"without its being used for conformity with another word; (M;) and this is extr.; (M, K;) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAb","text_ar":"باب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and a word of this measure has not a pl. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEilapN","text_ar":"اَفْعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by rule]. (M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbN","text_ar":"بَابٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAri","text_ar":"الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The door of the house"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbu Albayoti","text_ar":"بَابُ البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the door of the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the chamber,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbu Albaladi","text_ar":"بَابُ البَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the gate of the town"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"city"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (The Lexicons &c. passim.) And Bishr Ibn-Abee-Házim assigns a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAb","text_ar":"باب"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a grave; calling the latter a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) It is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an opening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a channel, made for water, to irrigate seed-produce:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abowaAbN","text_ar":"اَبْوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) [And in Egypt, it is applied also to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sepulchral chamber, grotto,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cave, hewn in a mountain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the Coptic"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"βηβ","text_ar":"βηβ","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biybaAnN","text_ar":"بِيبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only.] ―         -b2-  Hence, i. e. in a secondary application, the primary signification being “ a place of entrance, ” it is used as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A means of access,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of attainment, to a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(B, Kull, TK:) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEilomu baAbN A_ilaY Eilomi ka*aA","text_ar":"العِلْمُ بَابٌ اـِلَى عِلْمِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This science is a means of attainment to such a science."},{"kind":"text","text":"(B, TK.) ―         -b3-  [And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An expedient, a trick, a stratagem,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"process, by which something is to be effected"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abowaAbN","text_ar":"اَبْوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abowaAbu AlHarobi","text_ar":"اَبْوَابُ الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the expedients."},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."},{"kind":"page_break","n":273},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of war, battle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fight;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbN mina Aln~ujuwmi","text_ar":"بَابٌ مِنَ النُّجُومِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a process of the science of the stars,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"astrology"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"astronomy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbN mina Als~iHori","text_ar":"بَابٌ مِنَ السِّحْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a process of enchantment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siHorN","text_ar":"سِحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Compare Matt. xvi. 18,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"πύλαι ᾅδου οὐ κατισχύσουσιν αύτης","text_ar":"πύλαι ᾅδου οὐ κατισχύσουσιν αύτης","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":", probably meaning “ the stratagems of Hell shall not prevail against it. ”] ―         -b4-  [Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode, kind, sort, class,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"category."},{"kind":"text","text":"] Suweyd Ibn-Kuráa uses metaphorically the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abowaAb","text_ar":"اَبْوَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in relation to rhymes; saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^atayotu biA^abowaAbi AlqawaAfiY kaA^an~amaA\n                      \n                     \n                        A^a*uwdu bihaA sirobFA mina AlwaHo$i nuz~aEaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave utterance to the"},{"kind":"text","text":"various"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinds of rhymes as though I were driving with them a herd of wild animals desirous of the males,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of their wonted places of pasture"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, L.) [You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa mino h`*aA AlbaAbi","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنْ هٰذَا البَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is of this mode, kind, sort, class,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"category:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a phrase of frequent occurrence in lexicons &c. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbapN","text_ar":"بَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-  [Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chapter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a section,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subdivision, of a chapter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a book or writing;] conventionally, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece consisting of words relating to matters of one kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to matters of one species:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abowaAbN","text_ar":"اَبْوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbapN","text_ar":"بَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-  [Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"class of items"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"articles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in an account, or a reckoning; as in the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bay~anotu lahu HisaAbahu baAbFA baAbFA","text_ar":"بَيَّنْتُ لَهُ حِسَابَهُ بَابًا بَابًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I explained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made clear, to him his account,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reckoning, head by head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each class of items"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"articles by itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; a phrase mentioned by Sb: (M:) [or, sometimes,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbN","text_ar":"بَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbapN","text_ar":"بَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K) are used in relation to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huduwd","text_ar":"حُدُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which here means the punishments so termed], and to an account, or a reckoning, (T, M, K,) and the like, (T, M,) as signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extreme term"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAyapN","text_ar":"غَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) but IDrd hesitated respecting this, and therefore it is not mentioned in the S. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","MF","TA","S","K","B","Kull","TK","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}